snippet.textDisplay: So what will they do in Canada? There are some good things in the so-called "progressive" agenda.  But there are plenty of others that we've gotten an inkling of already that clearly, to many of us, are not actual "progress" at all.  But with plenty of charm, good looks, and heaps of social currency, M & R are guaranteed a sympathetic and eager audience for whatever they're going to be urging.  I have very deep reservations.
